hould Visit Nepal:</strong></h6>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Ethical tourism provides one of the largest sources of foreign revenue to Nepal. So, keeping the revenue flowing is key to rebuilding and survival.</li>\r\n	<li>A very large percentage of tourism jobs are held by people from earthquake affected areas, and it is estimated that one visiting tourist provides nine people with jobs.</li>\r\n	<li>A multitude of individuals in varying roles are sustained by tourists: those in hotels, transport companies, restaurants, airports, taxis, gear shops, souvenir stalls, not to mention the farmers who grow the food to supply the industry.</li>\r\n	<li>The multiplier effect of every dollar spent on travel in Nepal is immense.</li>\r\n	<li>Jobs and currency are the most needed long-term items for sustainable rebuilding.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h6><strong>Visa Information</strong></h6>\r\nYou can get a tourist visa on arrival, but you can count on a good hour of queuing at the immigration desk at theairport. Avoid this by getting a visa in your home country. You can also <a href=\"http://www.online.nepalimmigration.gov.np/tourist-visa\" target=\"_blank\">apply online here</a>. For further information check <a href=\"http://www.nepalimmigration.gov.np/\" target=\"_blank\">Nepal\'s Immigration website.</a> Indian visitors don\'t need to get the visa to enter Nepal, but bring your passport.'),(2013,79,'wpcf-right-box','<h6><strong>Weather</strong></h6>\r\nNepal\'s climate varies with the time of year and altitude. Ranging from the tropical to the arctic, when you visit mattersas much as where you visit. As a general rule, though, the lower you are, the hotter it gets, and the higher you climb,the fresher. Needless to say that high up in the himals during winter might leave you frozen, as much as a middaystroll in the Terai in July will make you suffocate. Play around with these variables and youll realise the best time ofthe year to visit the Kathmandu valley (1400m) is autumn. The monsoon clouds clear and leave the skies open forgorgeous mountain views and the temperatures drop to a perfectly nice average of 20C (70F) during the day.\r\n\r\nIn short: itll be dry, bring a sweater for the evenings, dont forget your sunscreen.\r\n<h6><strong>SIM Card Information</strong></h6>\r\nNcell and Nepal Telecom are the major mobile operators in Nepal. Both provide prepaid SIM card with data plans. You can find their outlets at Kathmandu airport, located in the arrival hall just before the exit. Bring one passport size photo and a photocopy of passport along with the original. You will be required to fill a simpleregistration form. Download <a href=\"http://www.ncell.com.np/Upload/images/Individual%20Subscription%20Form.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Ncell form</a> print it, fill it in and bring it to respective outlet.\r\n<h6><strong>CURRENCY</strong></h6>\r\nOne US Dollar buys you approximately 105 Nepali Rupees, making it pretty easy to convert local.\r\n\r\n* For Indian visitors - Rs. 500 and Rs. 1000 Indian currency notes are banned in Nepal, so bring Rs. 100 notes or $ which you can exchange in most tourist places without much hassle. Your credit/debit card should work, there are plenty of ATM around.'),(2015,188,'wpcf-link','http://www.theinnpatan.com'),(2017,168,'wpcf-link','http://www.yalaguesthouse.com'),(2018,172,'wpcf-link','http://www.theyellowhouse.com.np'),(2019,164,'wpcf-link','http://www.lalitheritagehome.com'),(2020,163,'wpcf-link','http://www.newachen.com'),(2021,171,'wpcf-link','http://www.blackpepperinn.com.np'),(2022,162,'wpcf-link','http://www.cosynepal.com'),(2024,80,'wpcf-link','http://www.traditionalhomes.com.np'),(2025,261,'_wp_attached_file','2015/09/photographing_the_everyday.jpg'),(2026,261,'_wp_attachment_metadata','a:5:{s:5:\"width\";i:1200;s:6:\"height\";i:377;s:4:\"file\";s:38:\"2015/09/photographing_the_everyday.jpg\";s:5:\"sizes\";a:4:{s:9:\"thumbnail\";a:4:{s:4:\"file\";s:38:\"photographing_the_everyday-150x150.jpg\";s:5:\"width\";i:150;s