:33','Art as a form can be classified into several genres, including those of painting, sculpture, performance, video and photography. While, there are definite overlaps of these forms borrowing from each other to create a work, how would one respond to a form becoming a base medium to create another form  as is the case with photography? The past two decades have seen an increasing shift in focus towards technology and new/ digital media intervening into various forms of contemporary art, where photography becomes a tool for the medium of conveyance into the creation of something further and is not always looked at as an end creation. This does not imply that photography does not stand as an individual art form; rather, it suggests the importance of photography as an extended language through medium in other forms of art. The medium of photography is freely used in artistic practices as materials, layers or photographic documentation.This conversation will discuss photography as an art form with varied approaches that work for and against it, and the levels of involvement of photography as an alternate and outside medium.','PHOTOGRAPHY AS AN ART FORM','','publish','closed','closed','','photography-as-an-art-form','','','2015-09-23 08:19:33','2015-09-23 02:34:33','',0,'http://localhost/pktm-event/?post_type=exhibition&#038;p=273',0,'exhibition','',0),(274,4,'2015-09-23 08:21:15','2015-09-23 02:36:15','Veerangana is an independent curator and art-writer; based in Mumbai, India. She studied English Literature (B.A) and holds post-graduate diplomas in Indian Aesthetics (2007) and Art Criticism and Theory (2009) as well as a Masters in History (2009) and was a participant of the first Gwangju Biennale Curators course (2009). Her curatorial experience has involved research on Emerging Asian and international artists and art practices, as well as Indian Modern and Contemporary Art. She was the recipient of the first IllySustainArt Curators prize (2011) and the 1st Annual ALICE (Artistic Landmark in Contemporary Experience) Publics Voice Award 2012 for best Emerging Curator.','VEERANGANA SOLANKI','','publish','closed','closed','','veerangana','','','2015-09-23 08:46:50','2015-09-23 03:01:50','',0,'http://localhost/pktm-event/?post_type=artist&#038;p=274',0,'artist','',0),(275,4,'2015-09-23 08:24:58','2015-09-23 02:39:58','DRAGANA JURISIC works predominantly through the medium of photography, film and installation. Her practice explores the issues of gender, stereotyping and the effects of exile and displacement on memory and identity. Since receiving a distinction for her MFA in 2008, Dragana Jurisic has won a significant number of awards including Dorothea Lange and Paul Taylor Awards Special Recognition from Duke University. In 2013, Dragana completed her PhD and completed an important three-year long project \'YU: The Lost Country\' that culminated in a critically acclaimed touring exhibition and a book. Her work is in many collections including Irish State Art Collection.','DRAGANA JURISIC','','publish','closed','closed','','dragana-jurisic','','','2015-09-23 08:37:12','2015-09-23 02:52:12','',0,'http://localhost/pktm-event/?post_type=artist&#038;p=275',0,'artist','',0),(276,4,'2015-09-23 08:26:28','2015-09-23 02:41:28','Yugoslavia fell apart in 1991. With the disappearance of the country, at least one million five hundred thousand Yugoslavs vanished. Today, in the countries that came into being after Yugoslavias disintegration, there is a total denial of the Yugoslav identity. Now, more than twenty years after the war(s) started, I feel safe to recall and question my own memories of both the place and the events I experienced.\r\n\r\nI am calling myself an exile, and not an expatriate  because I cant, even if I wanted to  return home. During the 1990 census, I was also denied the right to be Yugoslav, the nationality I had identified myself with since birth. Being a child of a Croatian father and a Serbian mother, this left me somewhat confused.\r\nYU: The Lost Country was originally conceived as a recreation of a homeland that was lost. It was a journey in which I would somehow draw a magical circle around the country that was once mine and in doing so, resurrect it, following Roland Barthes assertion that photography is more akin to magic than to art. Instead, it turned out to be a journey of rejection. My experience was one of displacement and a sense of exile that was stronger back home than in the foreign place where I had chosen to live. Photography contains elements such as fleetingness, which allow it to capture that sense of rootlessness and dislocation with relative ease. Both exile and photography intensify our perception of the world. In both, memory is in its underlying core. Both are characterized by melancholy. In Easter 2011, in search of both the lost country and a lost identity, I started retracing Wests journey and re-interpreting her masterpiece by using photography and text in an attempt to re-live my experience of Yugoslavia and to re-examine the conflicting emotions and memories of the country that was.','*** TITLE ***','','publish','closed','closed','','276','','','2015-09-23 08:26:59','2015-09-23 02:41:59','',0,'http://localhost/pktm-event/?post_type=exhibition&#038;p=276',0,'exhibition','',0),(279,4,'2015-09-23 08:37:07','2015-09-23 02:52:07','','Dragana-Jurisic---profile-pic','','inherit','open','closed','','dragana-jurisic-profile-pic','','','2015-09-23 08:37:07','2015-09-23 02:52:07','',275,'http://localhost/pktm-event/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Dragana-Jurisic-profile-pic.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(280,4,'2015-09-23 08:42:33','2015-09-23 02:57:33','Sren Pagter is the head of the world-renowned photojournalism education at the Danish School of Media and Journalism. Here, Sren Pagter has been teaching photojournalism to both Danish and international students for more than 16 years. Hes an educated press photographer and worked as such for ten years, before he dedicated his career to teaching photojournalism. Sren Pagter still does photographic projects and assignments to stay in touch with the media. Sren Pagter is lecturing and doing workshops all over the world  just like he has been in lots of different jurys, for instance POYi, The Danish Picture of the year, The Finnish Picture of the year, the Lumix Festival, etc.','SREN PAGTER','','publish','closed','closed','','soren-pagter','','','2015-09-23 11:01:59','2015-09-23 05:16:59','',0,'http://localhost/pktm-event/?post_type=artist&#038;p=280',0,'artist','',0),(281,4,'2015-09-23 08:43:39','2015-09-23 02:58:39','Lorem ispum','SUMIT DAYAL','','publish','closed','closed','','sumit-dayal','','','2015-09-23 11:33:22','2015-09-23 05:48:22','',0,'http://localhost/pktm-event/?post_type=artist&#038;p=281',0,'artist','',0),(282,4,'2015-09-23 08:44:32','2015-09-23 02:59:32','Lorem ipsum','THOMAS BORBERG','','publish','closed','closed','','thomas-borberg','','','2015-09-23 11:33:09','2015-09-23 05:48:09','',0,'http://localhost/pktm-event/?post_type=artist&#038;p=282',0,'artist','',0),(284,4,'2015-09-23 10:22:06','2015-09-23 04:37:06','','robert_godden - workshop_usingvisualmedia','','inherit','open','closed','','robert_godden-workshop_usingvisualmedia','','','2015-09-23 10:22:06','2015-09-23 04:37:06','',244,'http://localhost/pktm-event/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/robert_godden-workshop_usingvisualmedia.jpeg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(285,4,'2015-09-23 11:00:37','2015-09-23 05:15:37','','Soren Pagter','Photo by Anders Hviid','inherit','open','closed','','soren-pagter-profile','','','2015-09-23 11:01:23','2015-09-23 05:16:23','',280,'http://localhost/pktm-event/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Soren-Pagter-profile.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(286,4,'2015-09-23 11:07:11','2015-09-23 05:22:11','','Robert Godden','','inherit','open','closed','','robert_godden-profile_workshop_usingvisualmedia-2','','','2015-09-23 11:07:25','2015-09-23 05:22:25','',250,'http://localhost/pkt