alhost/pktm-event/?post_type=exhibition&p=294',0,'exhibition','',0),(295,4,'2015-09-24 14:30:00','2015-09-24 08:45:00','This 4-day workshop will train participants in the art of writing about oral history. Beginning with the oral history interview which urges and inspires the practice of deep listening, this workshop will focus on ways of attending to the story-telling strategies that people employ when speaking about their lives. The workshop will begin by focusing on theories of orality, memory and the nature of remembering and participants will be encouraged to reflect on these when they conduct their interviews. The practice of oral history demands an engagement with spoken memories, with subjectivity and feelings rather than objective truth. Participants will explore the ways in which photographs enable subjects to remember the past. Through practical engagements, the workshop will enable participants to transform spoken words into written words, focusing on the cultural context of language, and finally, explore the choices we make when writing about the oral history interview.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"color: #e6519d;\">COURSE HIGHLIGHTS</span></strong>\r\n\r\n Orality, memory and time; photographs as memory probes?\r\n Choices we make when transforming spoken to written language.\r\n Curating interviews\r\n Writing non-fiction and fiction based on oral history\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"color: #e6519d;\">WORKSHOP DETAILS</span></strong>\r\n\r\nDate: 27-30 October\r\nVenue: Yala Maya Kendra, Lalitpur\r\nTime: 9 am - 2 pm (Except on the last day)\r\nLanguage: English\r\nNo. of participants: 15 max.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"color: #e6519d;\">APPLICATION REQUIREMENT</span></strong>\r\n\r\nThe workshop is open to people from any background. Apart from the <a href=\"https://drive.google.com/open?id=0B1XMdR4hZTgmUjViZkZMOHdtb3c\" target=\"_blank\">application form</a>, the participants is also required to send an updated CV to mail@photoktm.com with the subject: Translating the Voice: Explorations in listening and writing.\r\n\r\nThe participants should also bring following to the workshop:\r\n Laptop\r\n A set of photographs from their family albums\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"color: #e6519d;\">WORKSHOP FEE</span></strong>: Rs.4000 (including VAT)\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"color: #e6519d;\">DEADLINE</span></strong>: 10 October, 2015','TRANSLATING THE VOICE: EXPLORATIONS IN LISTENING AND WRITING','','publish','closed','closed','','295','','','2015-09-24 14:38:41','2015-09-24 08:53:41','',0,'http://localhost/pktm-event/?post_type=exhibition&#038;p=295',0,'exhibition','',0),(296,4,'2015-09-24 14:32:05','2015-09-24 08:47:05','Lorem ipsum','INDIRA CHOWDHURY','','publish','closed','closed','','indira-chowdhury','','','2015-09-24 14:32:05','2015-09-24 08:47:05','',0,'http://localhost/pktm-event/?post_type=artist&#038;p=296',0,'artist','',0),(297,4,'2015-09-24 14:33:53','2015-09-24 08:48:53','This 4-day workshop will train participants in the art of writing about oral history. Beginning with the oral history interview which urges and inspires the practice of deep listening, this workshop will focus on ways of attending to the story-telling strategies that people employ when speaking about their lives. The workshop will begin by focusing on theories of orality, memory and the nature of remembering and participants will be encouraged to reflect on these when they conduct their interviews. The practice of oral history demands an engagement with spoken memories, with subjectivity and feelings rather than objective truth. Participants will explore the ways in which photographs enable subjects to remember the past. Through practical engagements, the workshop will enable participants to transform spoken words into written words, focusing on the cultural context of language, and finally, explore the choices we make when writing about the oral history interview.\n\nCOURSE HIGHLIGHTS\n\n Orality, memory and time; photographs as me